section(class="template-wrapper")
    aside(class="template-asideLeft o-aside-Item")
    |
    |
    div(class="template-section m-a")
        section(class="template-content")
            
             div(class="row")
                div(class="row-flex mt30 align-items-center")
                    div(class="col-flex-sm12 col-flex-md5 col-center p10")
                        img(src="./unit_3/module_9/assets/images/self_6_1.png", alt="", srcset="" class="u-responsive-img centrado w70")

                    div(class="col-flex-sm12 col-flex-md7 col-center") 
                        div(class="row")
                            p(class="u-txtSpace")
                            p
                            h5 Choose the option that best completes the sentences.
                            p
                                strong Employee:
                                |  I would like to talk about my holidays for this year. Could I have them in December?

                            p
                                strong Employer:
                                |  That's a possibility
                                strong  (1)
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_1" name="tfInputRadio_1" value="1")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_1" class="c-CheckSelected") provided 
                                | /
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_2" name="tfInputRadio_1" value="2")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_2" class="c-CheckSelected") unless
                                | too many people decide to take them in December, too.

                            p
                                strong Employee: 
                                | But
                                strong  (2)
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_3" name="tfInputRadio_2" value="1")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_3" class="c-CheckSelected") if
                                | /
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_4" name="tfInputRadio_2" value="2")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_4" class="c-CheckSelected") provided
                                | you know I am asking first, could I have the priority?

                            p
                                strong Employer:
                                |   Hmmm, the problem is that you have been working here for 7 months. That’s why I say that
                                strong  (3)
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_5" name="tfInputRadio_3" value="1")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_5" class="c-CheckSelected") unless
                                | /
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10 mt10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_6" name="tfInputRadio_3" value="2")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_6" class="c-CheckSelected") providing
                                | other people with more years in the company don’t ask for the same dates, that will be ok.

                            p
                                strong Employee:
                                |  I understand but what
                                strong  (4)
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_7" name="tfInputRadio_4" value="1")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_7" class="c-CheckSelected") if
                                | /
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_8" name="tfInputRadio_4" value="2")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_8" class="c-CheckSelected") provided
                                | they decide at the last moment?

                            p
                                strong Employer:
                                |  Good point. I will tell them that
                                strong  (5)
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_9" name="tfInputRadio_5" value="1")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_9" class="c-CheckSelected") unless
                                | /
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_10" name="tfInputRadio_5" value="2")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_10" class="c-CheckSelected") provided
                                | they inform me before November 15, I cannot guarantee holidays in December.

                            p
                                strong Employee:
                                |  I think that's fair. But, then,
                                strong  (6)
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_11" name="tfInputRadio_6" value="1")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_11" class="c-CheckSelected") if
                                | /
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_12" name="tfInputRadio_6" value="2")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_12" class="c-CheckSelected") unless
                                | they decide they really want their holiday in December, could I take them in January?

                            p
                                strong Employer:
                                |  Sure,
                                strong  (7)
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_13" name="tfInputRadio_7" value="1")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_13" class="c-CheckSelected") providing
                                | /
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_14" name="tfInputRadio_7" value="2")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_14" class="c-CheckSelected") unless
                                | we have enough people to cover for the job. You need to understand that by law, you can only take your holidays
                                strong  (8)
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_15" name="tfInputRadio_8" value="1")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_15" class="c-CheckSelected") provided
                                | /
                                span(class="c-textField ml10 mr10 mb10")
                                    input(class="c-inputRadio" type="radio" id="inputRadio_16" name="tfInputRadio_8" value="2")
                                    label(for="inputRadio_16" class="c-CheckSelected") unless
                                | you have a year in the company.




